<P>
MEXICO VOLCANO ERUPTS; NO INJURIES REPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 13,000-foot Colima volcano in western Mexico erupted in a towering cloud 
of ash and rocks that forced those living near the flanks to flee. 
</P>
<P>
 No injuries or deaths were reported. 
</P>
<P>
 No signs of new volcanic activity emerged Friday and about 500 people returned 
home following the Thursday night scare. 
</P>
<P>
 The volcano lies in a mountainous area 440 miles west of Mexico City near the 
Pacific coast. 
</P>
