POSTAL EMPLOYEE ADMITS HE THREW AWAY MAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A South Carolina mail carrier confessed to throwing away mail he would not 
have been able to deliver on time, local radio and television reported Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Postal officials said the part-time mail carrier told them he discarded the 
mail on July 6 because he could not finish his route on time. The man was not 
identified. 
</P>
<P>
 A jogger spotted the bundles of mail along a wooded area Tuesday and called 
postal officials. They confronted the employee at his home, where he confessed 
to dumping more than 500 pieces of mail, and immediately resigned. 
</P>
