<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME DON'T LIKE GAME, OTHERS DON'T LIKE WAY WORLD CUP FINAL ENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Until two months ago, I, like most American sports fans, was ignorant about 
soccer, considered it the most boring sport on Earth and could not understand 
its worldwide appeal. 
</P>
<P>
 With the coming of the World Cup to the United States, I decided to learn the 
rules and tactics of the game, the skills involved and the strengths and 
weaknesses of the better teams. I attended two games at the Rose Bowl and 
watched many more on television. 
</P>
<P>
 Now I can say that I was wrong. Backed by a basic understanding of the game, I 
readily admit that soccer, when played at its highest levels, is every bit as 
exciting as "Bowling for Dollars." 
</P>
<P>
 RICHARD G. SIMON 
