Angel errors are not limited to the playing field because I believe Jimmie 
Reese was Jewish. 
</P>
<P>
 A Times article several years ago contained an anecdote about a celebrity 
baseball game in the 1940s. Songwriter Harry Ruby was pitching and told his 
catcher to dispense with the signs and just call out the pitches in Yiddish, 
since the batters would not understand this language. When Jimmie Reese came to 
