<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA; ONE OF TWO 
WOMEN HELD IN MAN'S KIDNAPING RELEASED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One woman was released and another woman remained in custody Friday in 
connection with the kidnaping of a 26-year-old Pasadena man. 
</P>
<P>
 Laura Melgar, 28, of Los Angeles was released from jail Thursday night pending 
further investigation, police said. Walella Mayson, 32, of Norwalk remains in 
the Pasadena City Jail on suspicion of kidnaping Robert Gray, general manager 
at the Edmund A. Gray Co., a Los Angeles manufacturing company. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators still want to question Melgar's husband, an ex-employee of the 
Edmund A. Gray Co., and Mayson's boyfriend. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Gray was accosted at gunpoint Tuesday morning as he was leaving his 
Pasadena condominium to go to work. The abductors left him about 16 hours later 
in South-Central Los Angeles. 
