<P>
 A memorial service for a single father killed this week when a 2,000-pound 
pipe tore off the roof of his vehicle as he drove on the Golden State Freeway 
is scheduled for 3 p.m. today at Blessed Sacrament Catholic Church, 6657 Sunset 
Blvd., Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 Charles Fedorko, 46, died Tuesday afternoon when a truck carrying 27 of the 
heavy pipes lost its load on a Foothill Freeway transition ramp 45 feet above 
traffic on the Golden State Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
 He was an executive with Keystone Communications in Los Angeles, which 
distributes television programs nationwide by satellite. 
</P>
<P>
 Fedorko had lived for the past two years with his 14-year-old son, David, in 
the Stevenson Ranch housing complex just west of Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the accident is still under investigation. 
