<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; DODGERS; CLAIRE LOOKING FOR A YOUNG LEFT-HANDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fred Claire might not want to give up any young, quality players to acquire a 
veteran left-hander such as Randy Myers or John Franco, but the comments made 
by the club's executive vice president Friday indicate that he is searching for 
a young, quality pitcher for the bullpen. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have talked with every American League and National League scout the last 
couple of days who have been out looking at our needs," Claire said. "The ideal 
move for any club is to make a move involving young quality players. If I had 
the choice of a quality veteran player or a younger one, I would take a younger 
one." 
</P>
<P>
 Claire, when asked if the search included any left-handers said: "I know all 
their names." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Orel Hershiser played catch for the third time since straining a muscle in his 
rib cage and will probably throw off the mound Sunday. If all goes well, he 
will pitch Tuesday against the Giants in San Francisco. . . . Tom Candiotti 
will pitch tonight, making his third appearance in eight games. During his last 
two appearances, which came two days apart, he gave up only two unearned runs 
in 13 innings for a 1.38 earned-run average. Those are the only two games the 
Dodgers have won on this trip. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Treadway was ejected from Friday night's game during the sixth inning by 
third base umpire Larry Vanover, who didn't appreciate a comment made by 
Treadway from the dugout. One of the Dodger relievers had yelled something to 
Vanover after he called a ball hit by a Dodger foul. Vanover walked over to the 
end of the dugout, where the relievers were sitting, to find out who made the 
comment. Meanwhile, the game continued. "He had called time out, but the game 
was still going on," bullpen coach Mark Cresse said. None of the Dodger 
relievers would confess, and Treadway, walking toward that end of the dugout, 
yelled to Vanover that the game was going on. "He was over there while the 
pitch was being thrown, so I yelled, 'Hey, the game is going on,' " Treadway 
said. "He said, 'One more word and you are out of here.' I still don't know why 
he threw me out." MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072394-0134 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 063283 </DOCID>
