<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANTLEY TO RIDE IN HOLLYWOOD JUVENILE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Antley has picked up the mount on Sierra Diablo in Monday's $100,000 
Hollywood Juvenile, according to trainer Mark Hennig. 
</P>
<P>
 Sierra Diablo has raced just once, but it was a memorable effort.The son of 
Conquistador Cielo rallied strongly to post a one-length victory over Chief 
Capote in a maiden special weight race on June 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddie Delahoussaye was aboard as Sierra Diablo timed 58 seconds for five 
furlongs in the victory. Delahoussaye, however, is out of action until later 
next week after undergoing surgery to correct a sinus problem, and the mount on 
Sierra Diablo opened up for Antley. 
</P>
<P>
 Antley began Friday in fourth place in the jockey standings with 60 wins and 
tied with Chris McCarron for first in stakes wins at seven apiece. 
</P>
<P>
 The probable field for the Juvenile Championship, to be decided at six 
furlongs: Cold N Calculating, Pedroza; Cyrano, Corey Nakatani; Fox Mountain, 
Garrett Gomez; Mr Purple, Chris McCarron; Serena's Song, Gary Stevens; Sierra 
Diablo, Antley, and Tyson's Revenge, Fernando Valenzuela. 
</P>
