<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; INMATE, 44, DIES OF UNKNOWN CAUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 44-year-old Oxnard woman died of an unknown cause while in custody at 
Ventura County Jail, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Maria Gloria Mendez, an unemployed seamstress, was pronounced dead at Ventura 
County Medical Center at 11:32 p.m. Thursday, about two hours after she was 
discovered unconscious in the medical ward at the jail, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura County Deputy Coroner Dale Zentzis said an autopsy performed Friday 
did not reveal the cause of death. Authorities are waiting for results of 
toxicology and tissue tests, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mendez was arrested for using drugs and booked by Oxnard police on a warrant 
about 8:30 p.m. Wednesday, Ventura County Sheriff's Lt. Craig Husband said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mendez was under the influence of alcohol and heroin at the time and was put 
in the jail's medical ward, Husband said. 
</P>
<P>
 "She had medical problems related to drugs, and abscesses on her leg, and they 
wanted to monitor her," Husband said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mendez was put into a single-person cell and given medication to relieve her 
pain, Husband said. Nurses checked her vital signs periodically and monitored 
her through an intercom, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 When they checked her vital signs about 9 p.m. Thursday, they appeared normal, 
Husband said. Nurses then continued to monitor her through an intercom and in a 
routine check about 45 minutes later, Mendez was found unconscious. 
</P>
<P>
 She was then taken to Ventura County Medical Center, where she died. PEGGY Y. 
LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
