<P>
LEE LOSES TITLE BY ONE STROKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton's Jenny Lee finished second at the Optimist Junior World golf 
championship Friday in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee, playing in the girls' 15-17 division, shot par 74 and finished a stroke 
behind Shauna Estes of Orangeburg, S.C. Estes made a 10-foot birdie putt on the 
18th hole at Torrey Pines North for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee and Estes were tied going into the 16th hole, where Lee three-putted and 
fell one stroke behind. Lee pulled even on 17, but missed a 15-foot putt for 
birdie on 18. 
</P>
<P>
 Estes had a four-round total of four-under 292; Lee finished at 293. 
</P>
