<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALSA BEATS VANCOUVER IN OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Salsa defeated the Vancouver 86ers, 2-1, in overtime Friday in front of 
4,802 at Vancouver's Swangard Stadium to move into first place in the American 
Professional Soccer League. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Wright scored from 13 yards in the seventh minute of overtime to give the 
Salsa (3-2) its third consecutive victory.Wright's goal was set up by a long 
kick by goalkeeper Paul Littman, who was credited with an assist. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is without a doubt the best team effort of the season," Salsa Coach Rick 
Davis said. "The players played with discipline and determination. We have been 
working hard, and the hard work paid off in the second half and in the 
overtime." 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa tied the score, 1-1, early in the second half when Waldir Guerra 
scored after a pass from Wright. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa has 23 points. Second-place Colorado has 21 and Vancouver is third 
with 19. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa's home opener is 6 p.m. Sunday against the Seattle Sounders at Titan 
Stadium. 
</P>
